body: For try-with-resource you should check if this case shows up: This is a false positive and should not be refactored.

@barthanssens  I hope you don't mind. After checking for try-with-resource with the intellij inspection I ended up fixing a couple of them.

https://github.com/eclipse/rdf4j/pull/1644
`isEmpty() instead of size() == 0` will probably lead to some performance improvements ;)

Not at all :-) Most of the try-with-resources were fixed in a previous run
 
Most issues Netbeans I/T noticed are suggestions to use diamond inference, and using multi catch instead of multiple catch blocks repeating the same code

And a list of suggestions to make fields final
